article.headline: Liberty 64, Coker 49
article.story: LYNCHBURG, Va. (AP) -- Anthony Smith scored 16 points and pulled down 11 rebounds as Liberty beat Coker 64-49 Tuesday night in its home opener. Coker (0-1) started out good when Lukas Varga stole the ball and hit a layup, but the Cobras didn't score again for almost five minutes. The Flames led by as many as 18 in the first half before taking a 41-30 lead into the break. Liberty (1-3) held the Cobras to 19 points in the second half and wouldn't allow them to get closer than 9. Kyle Ohman and Alex McLean each added 15 for the Flames. Ohman's points came off five 3-pointers. J.C. Hafner led Coker with 15 points, including four from beyond the arc.
